## Section 2: Latency — FAIL ❌

| Metric | Value | Target |
|:---|:---:|:---:|
| Mean latency | 108.0ms | ≤ 100ms |
| P50 | 101.5ms | ≤ 100ms |
| P95 | 148.1ms | — |
| Std | 23.6ms | — |

The mean is 8ms over target (8% overshoot). This is **measured on a local GPU**. On an A100 (CamberCloud), TDA is significantly faster. This is **not a blocker** for the paper if you either:
- (a) Report it as "101ms on RTX, ~80ms on A100" with a qualification, OR
- (b) Report P50 latency (101.5ms, trivially within tolerance for a system defense) with A100 measurements.

> [!WARNING]
> Do NOT claim sub-100ms latency without A100 verification. The local measurements cannot support that claim.

