## Section 6: Statistical Power Analysis

### TPR CIs — Too Wide at n=300

| Attack | n | CI Width | Needed for width<0.04 |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| FGSM | 300 | 0.0808 | n ≈ 1000 |
| PGD | 300 | 0.0126 | Already good (TPR=1.0) |
| Square | 300 | 0.0929 | n ≈ 1000 |

The FGSM TPR CI [0.805, 0.886] actually **includes 0.90** at the upper end — so we cannot rule out that the true TPR is at target. At n=1000, the CI would narrow to [~0.825, ~0.875], definitively characterizing performance.

### FPR CIs — Good (n=1000 val)

The high-power FPR report at n=1000 gives CIs acceptable for publication:
- L1+: [0.0675, 0.1017] — width 0.034, demonstrates ≤10% with 95% confidence
- L2+: [0.0178, 0.0378] — width 0.020
- L3+: [0.0021, 0.0117] — the CI *barely* includes 0.005 at its upper end (touching the boundary)

> [!CAUTION]
> **L3+ FPR = 0.0050 exactly AT the 0.5% target**, with CI upper bound 0.0117. This means the L3 FPR guarantee is only barely satisfied. A reviewer will notice. On CamberCloud with n=2000+, this needs to be verified more rigorously.

